<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 8600 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - SPLASH PANELS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>SPLASH PANELS</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Splash Panel- Removal</title>
            <para>The splash panels (
                <hotlnk document="s09008_4.xml" xrefid="f0900804">Figure 4</hotlnk>) on the 8600 series minimize splash
                and mud, protecting vital engine systems from corrosion and malfunction.
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>Splash Panel Removal - Drivers Side</title>
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tilt the hood assembly forward and locate the splash panel mounting bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900829">Figure 29, Item 4</hotlnk>) at the forward lower section of the splash
                    panel. Loosen and remove the splash panel mounting bolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the forward upper splash panel mounting bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900829">Figure 29, Item 2</hotlnk>). Loosen and remove the mounting bolts
                    attaching the splash panel to the upper section of the hood assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the rear splash panel mounting bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900829">Figure 29, Item 7</hotlnk>), loosen and remove.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the splash panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the hood tilted locate the driver side 2 forward mounting bolts (
                    <hotlnk document="s09008_12.xml" xrefid="f0900820">Item 2</hotlnk>) attaching the splash panel to
                    the front hood assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the bolts and lock washers.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the 2 rear splash panel mounting bolts and lock washers located along the upper
                    edge of the splash panel.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the splash panel assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900829" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900829.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 29. Splash Panel Removal (Driver Side Shown)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HOOD</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SPLASH PANEL FORWARD, UPPER MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HOOD HARNESS</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. SPLASH PANEL FORWARD, LOWER MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. SPLASH PANEL</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. FENDER SECTION</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. UPPER REAR SPLASH PANEL MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Splash Panel - Install</title>
            <para>Beginning on the passenger side:</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the splash panel mounting holes with the hood mounting holes (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900830">Figure 30, Item 1</hotlnk>) insert the mounting bolts and lock washers.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Hand tighten only.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the lower mounting holes with the inner fender section (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900829">Figure 29, Item 7</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the mounting bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900830">Figure 30, Item 1</hotlnk>) and lock washers.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the splash panel mounting bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten to 125 to 140 in-lbs (14 to 16 Nm).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900830" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900830.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 30. Splash Panel Remove/Install (Passenger Side Shown)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HOOD TILT ASSIST CYLINDER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SPLASH PANEL MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SPLASH PANEL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the hood / fender splash panel on the inner fender of the hood / fender
                    assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900831">Figure 31, Item 5</hotlnk>). Install the 2 forward mounting bolts and lock
                    washer to the hood / fender assembly.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0900831" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900831.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                             scalefitheight="232px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 31. Splash Panel Install (Driver Side Shown)</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. SPLASH SHIELD</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. HOOD TILT ASSIST CYLINDER</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. HOOD HARNESS</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. TORSION ASSIST BAR</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. SPLASH SHIELD FORWARD MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the 2 rear splash panel mounting holes in place on the hood and install the
                    mounting bolts and lock washers. Securing it to the hood assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the bolts to the required torque.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten to 125 to 140 in-lbs (14 to 16 Nm).</para>
            </step1>
            <para></para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Close hood and secure the hood latches.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
